---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Window Replacement Cranbourne | Aluminium & Sliding Doors | (03) 9003 0108"
  description="Window and sliding-door replacement across Cranbourne, Cranbourne East, Cranbourne West and Cranbourne North — for 80s–2000s aluminium swap-outs and new-estate stacker-door upgrades."
  canonical="https://berwickwindowreplacement.com.au/cranbourne/">

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <span class="hero-eyebrow">Cranbourne &middot; Cranbourne East &middot; Cranbourne West &middot; Cranbourne North</span>
      <h1>Window replacement in <span class="accent">Cranbourne</span>.</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        Cranbourne is the City of Casey&rsquo;s biggest suburb by volume and
        the widest spread by housing age. Older Cranbourne and Cranbourne West
        houses from the 1970s&ndash;90s often still have the original aluminium
        or steel-frame windows &mdash; condensation, seized winders, single
        pane. Cranbourne East and Clyde North new builds are the opposite end:
        big openings, big sliding doors, owners upgrading to bigger.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030108">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0108</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Book a free measure</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <span class="section-eyebrow">Why Cranbourne</span>
      <h2>The Cranbourne window story.</h2>
      <div class="divider"></div>
      <div style="max-width: 65rem;">
        <h3>Two markets, two conversations.</h3>
        <p>
          Older Cranbourne (around the racecourse, west of South Gippsland
          Highway, north up to Centre Road) was built progressively from
          the 1970s through the 90s. The window stock here is the oldest in
          Casey: steel-frame casements that rust at the corners, single-pane
          aluminium that&rsquo;s well past 30 years of UV, sliding windows
          where the rollers gave out a decade ago and now they&rsquo;re
          jammed open or held with a cut broomstick. These are full
          frame-replacement jobs, not glass-only.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Cranbourne East &amp; Clyde North new estates.</h3>
        <p>
          The big new-build belt &mdash; Cranbourne East, Clyde North, Clyde,
          Cranbourne South &mdash; runs from roughly 2014 to current. Standard
          builder-spec windows are decent here (energy-rated, double-glazing
          increasingly standard from 2020 onwards) so the jobs we get tend to
          be: upsizing the rear sliding door, adding a kitchen-side awning
          window for cross-flow, or correcting a builder mistake where the
          living-room window was specced too small. Big sliding-door
          upgrades (2.4m to 3.6m or 4.2m) are the most common ask.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Class M / H reactive clay (most of Cranbourne).</h3>
        <p>
          The same Cranbourne reactive clay that cracks driveways will also
          twist a window frame if the wall studs above the opening have moved
          out of square. On older houses we check the head and sill for racking
          before ordering &mdash; an extra 5mm fudge factor in the frame size
          either way saves a remake. Newer estate homes on engineered slabs
          have less movement and tighter tolerances work fine.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Typical Cranbourne jobs.</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>1970s&ndash;90s house full re-window, 14&ndash;18 windows ($14K&ndash;$22K)</li>
          <li>Rust-out steel-frame removal + aluminium replacement (per window $700&ndash;$1,400)</li>
          <li>Cranbourne East rear-door upgrade 2.4m &rarr; 3.6m stacker ($4.5K&ndash;$6.5K)</li>
          <li>Builder-spec window upsize (per opening $1,200&ndash;$2,400)</li>
          <li>Kitchen + bathroom awning swap-out (4 windows $1.8K&ndash;$3.6K)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h2>Other service areas.</h2>
      <div class="areas-grid">
        <a class="area-pill" href="/berwick/">Berwick</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/narre-warren/">Narre Warren</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/hampton-park/">Hampton Park</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/endeavour-hills/">Endeavour Hills</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/city-of-casey/">All City of Casey</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="cta-block">
        <h2>Free Cranbourne window measure-up.</h2>
        <p>Older-house full re-window vs new-build sliding-door upgrade &mdash; honest pricing both ways.</p>
        <div class="hero-actions" style="justify-content:center;">
          <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030108">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0108</a>
          <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Book online</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
